@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1 class="mb-3">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your personal information
    when you use this application. By accessing or using our website, you agree to the terms
    described below.
</p>

<h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
<p>
    As part of the ASP.NET Core Identity system, we may collect:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Full Name</li>
    <li>Email Address</li>
    <li>Password (securely hashed)</li>
    <li>Login history and security information</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. How Your Information Is Used</h3>
<p>
    Your information is only used for:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>User registration and authentication</li>
    <li>Maintaining secure access to your account</li>
    <li>Improving system performance and security</li>
    <li>Password recovery and account notifications</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Cookies and Session Usage</h3>
<p>
    We use cookies and session storage to:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Keep you logged in securely</li>
    <li>Store temporary preferences</li>
    <li>Protect your login session from unauthorized access</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Data Storage and Security</h3>
<p>
    All passwords are stored using strong hashing algorithms. We use SSL/TLS encryption
    to protect data transmitted between your browser and our servers.
</p>

<h3>5. Sharing of Information</h3>
<p>
    We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties
    unless required by law or for security investigations.
</p>

<h3>6. Your Rights</h3>
<p>You may request:</p>
<ul>
    <li>To view your account information</li>
    <li>To update your personal data</li>
    <li>To delete your account (if supported)</li>
</ul>

<h3>7. Contact Information</h3>
<p>
    For questions or concerns about your privacy, please contact the administrator
    or support team of this application.
</p>
